The Global Citizen Festival, whose first edition took place in 2012, is an extension of the Global Poverty Project, an international advocacy group that hopes to eradicate poverty by increasing the number of people actively fighting it.
In order to receive a free ticket to the event (unless you're willing to pay for a VIP ticket), viewers had to complete a series of tasks, or "actions," such as volunteering, sending an email to a world leader, calling or making any other useful effort in order to raise awareness of the fight against poverty.
But to what extent can the Global Citizen organization still achieve its goal in the remaining 12 years?
