The group also said that as a result of the company’s more than 5,000 actions to ask the UK to improve maternal and child nutrition, the government announced funding for a project, The Power of Nutrition, which will benefit 5 million women and children as part of nutritional interventions.
In response to one of the most frequently asked questions on its website, “What makes you think it’s possible to end extreme poverty?”,
Global Citizen said: “The road to get there will be long and difficult, sometimes we will fall and we will fail.
However, like the great civil rights movements and the struggle against apartheid before us, we will get there because we are more powerful together.
