The claim would be disputed by some journalists: Since September 10, Sanders has not held a press conference at the White House.
Host Chris Wallace asked why.
Sanders responded that the rarity of the talks was not due to a dislike for “demagogic” TV reporters, although she said, “I don’t mind the fact that they’re scaring the gallery.”
Then she hinted that direct contact between Trump and the press would increase.
Without citing evidence, she added that “the president is participating in more question-and-answer sessions than any other president before him”: “We checked the numbers.”
There will always be press conferences, Sanders said, but “if the press has the chance to directly question the president of the United States, it’s infinitely better than talking to me.
